Two people were injured in Bloemfontein following two separate collisions in the early hours of Sunday morning. One person sustained moderate injuries after two vehicles collided in Dr Belcher Road.  The patient was stabilised on scene by paramedics before being transported to Pelonomi Hospital for further care.  The other occupants sustained minor or no injuries and refused further care.  In the second Bloemfontein crash on the same day a motorist was fortunate to escape with only minor injuries after colliding with a tree on the N8 close to East End.  He was treated on scene by paramedics before being transported to 3 Military Hospital for further care.   Stanley Schimper of Trauma Response Africa said both accidents happened in the early hours of Sunday morning. Authorities are investigating the cause of the crashes.